    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>brown onion[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then put the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in the oven for 10-15 min or until they have softened</p><p>Tip: You don't want the potatoes to brown at this point!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>While the potatoes are cooking, trim your<strong> green beans</strong>, then add them to a pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>(just enough to cover them)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and rinse the beans under <strong>cold water</strong> and set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and your <strong>red wine paste</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and set it aside for later \u2013 this is your<strong> red wine stock</strong></p><p>Warm 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[120ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> in the <strong>microwave </strong>and stir through your <strong>clotted cream</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>clotted cream mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have softened, layer the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> in an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then pour your <strong>clotted cream mixture</strong> all over and sprinkle with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until golden and crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>dauphinoise potatoes</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your<strong> sirloin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>sirloin steak[s]</strong> to the pan, for rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side: for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side: for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Once the steak is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest (reserve the pan!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the steak is cooking, return the pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained green beans</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further \u2013 these are your <strong>garlicky green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the steak is resting, return the pan to a medium-high heat with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs until you're left with a sandy-paste</p><p>Add the <strong>red wine stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has reduced to a gravy-like consistency</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>red wine sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Butter helps to thicken the sauce and give it a great shine!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested sirloin steak </strong>finely on a clean board</p><p>Served the <strong>sliced sirloin steak</strong> with the <strong>dauphinoise potatoes</strong> and <strong>garlicky green beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Pour the <strong>red wine sauce</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
